article.description: Marcus Gilbert scored 21 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Fairfield to a 97-85 win over Dartmouth on Monday night.
article.headline: Fairfield pulls away from Dartmouth, 97-85
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. -- Marcus Gilbert scored 21 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Fairfield to a 97-85 win over Dartmouth on Monday night. Jerry Johnson Jr. and Tyler Nelson each finished with 20 points and Curtis Cobb added 16 points and four assists for Fairfield (7-6). The Stags shot 55.9 percent from the field, hit 12 3-pointers, and finished with 19 total assists as a team. After Connor Boehm hit a jumper to give Dartmouth (4-8) a 59-58 lead with 11:48 left in the game, Fairfield went on 17-6 run over the ensuing five minutes to grab a 75-65 lead. Seven of the 16 points came from Johnson Jr. Dartmouth never seriously threatened the rest of the night. Gilbert added a 3-point play to extend the Fairfield lead to a game-high 14 (97-83) with 35 seconds left. Boehm finished with 24 points for the Big Green.
